title: ByungHo Park hits 2-run shot, Minnesota Twins top Marlins
text:
More Park hits 2-run shot, Twins top Marlins Minnesota Twins slugger Byung Ho Park hits a two-run home run off Miami Marlins starting pitcher Jose Urena. AP/Copyright The Associated Press. All rights reserved. Feb 27, 2017 at 7:13p ET 0Shares 
ByungHo Park hit a two-run homer, his second shot since being dropped him from the 40-man roster earlier this month, to help the Minnesota Twins to a 9-6 win over the Miami Marlins. 
Twins starter Ervin Santana struck out two in two scoreless innings. 
Tyler Moore homered for Marlins starter Jose Urena gave up two runs in an inning. 0
